Can we remove the `;` and make it two lines please? Everything else in this file is written "one tactic a line".
Oooops. It looks like a refactor somebody did after me.
Apparently it comes straight from #6385 ! Maybe past Martin would disapprove current Martin 😆
This is afaik used only in one section. Can we move it there please?
It's used in two sections, actually

```suggestion
@[simp] lemma derives_reverse_comm : g.reverse.Derives u v ↔ g.Derives u.reverse v.reverse := by
```
I thought I already fixed this typo. Apparently, it was on the other branch.
